# {{projectName}}

A REST API built with [DartAPI](https://pub.dev/packages/dartapi_core).

## Project Structure

```
bin/main.dart        # Server entrypoint
lib/src/
  config/            # AppConfig, EnvConfig, env_loader
  controllers/       # AuthController, UserController, ProductController
  core/              # DartAPI server class, RouterManager
  dto/               # Request/response DTOs
  models/            # Domain models
env/                 # Environment files
  .env.example       # Committed — documents all available variables
  .env.dev           # Local dev overrides (gitignored)
  .env.staging       # Staging overrides (gitignored)
  .env.uat           # UAT overrides (gitignored)
  .env.production    # Production overrides (gitignored)
migrations/          # Numbered .sql migration files
test/                # Controller tests
```

## Environment Setup

The server loads `.env` (base values) then `.env.<APP_ENV>` (environment overrides).
`Platform.environment` variables always take priority over file values.

| Environment | File | `APP_ENV` value |
|---|---|---|
| Development | `env/.env.dev` | `dev` |
| Staging | `env/.env.staging` | `staging` |
| UAT | `env/.env.uat` | `uat` |
| Production | `env/.env.production` | `production` |

Copy `.env.example` to get started:

```bash
cp env/.env.example env/.env.dev
# edit env/.env.dev with your local database credentials
```

**Never commit `env/.env.*` files.** Only `env/.env.example` is tracked by git.

## Running the Server

### Development (default)

```bash
dart run bin/main.dart
```

With an explicit environment or custom port:

```bash
APP_ENV=dev dart run bin/main.dart --port=3000
```

### Staging

```bash
APP_ENV=staging dart run bin/main.dart
```

### UAT

```bash
APP_ENV=uat dart run bin/main.dart
```

### Production

Set real secrets via environment variables (do **not** rely on `.env.production` for secrets in CI/CD):

```bash
export APP_ENV=production
export DB_HOST=your-db-host
export DB_NAME={{projectName}}_production
export DB_USER=your-db-user
export DB_PASSWORD=your-db-password
export JWT_ACCESS_SECRET=$(openssl rand -hex 32)
export JWT_REFRESH_SECRET=$(openssl rand -hex 32)
dart run bin/main.dart
```

Or compile to a self-contained native binary:

```bash
dart compile exe bin/main.dart -o {{projectName}}
APP_ENV=production ./{{projectName}}
```

## Environment Variables Reference

| Variable | Dev default | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `APP_ENV` | `dev` | Active environment: `dev` / `staging` / `uat` / `production` |
| `PORT` | `8080` | HTTP server port |
| `DEBUG` | `true` | Print startup info (`false` in production) |
| `LOG_LEVEL` | `debug` | `debug` / `info` / `warn` / `error` |
| `DB_HOST` | `localhost` | PostgreSQL host |
| `DB_PORT` | `5432` | PostgreSQL port |
| `DB_NAME` | `{{projectName}}_dev` | Database name |
| `DB_USER` | `postgres` | Database user |
| `DB_PASSWORD` | `yourpassword` | Database password |
| `DB_POOL_SIZE` | `5` (dev), `20` (prod) | Max connection pool size |
| `JWT_ACCESS_SECRET` | *(dev placeholder)* | **Must be changed in production** |
| `JWT_REFRESH_SECRET` | *(dev placeholder)* | **Must be changed in production** |
| `JWT_ACCESS_EXPIRY_MINUTES` | `60` (dev), `15` (prod) | Access token lifetime |
| `JWT_REFRESH_EXPIRY_DAYS` | `30` (dev), `7` (prod) | Refresh token lifetime |
| `CORS_ORIGIN` | `*` (dev), `''` (prod) | Allowed CORS origin (`*` = any, `''` = same-origin) |

## API Endpoints

### Auth

| Method | Path | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `POST` | `/auth/login` | Obtain access + refresh tokens |
| `POST` | `/auth/refresh` | Exchange a refresh token for a new access token |
| `POST` | `/auth/logout` | Revoke the refresh token |

### Users *(Bearer token required)*

| Method | Path | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `GET` | `/users` | List users (`?page=1&limit=10`) |
| `POST` | `/users` | Create a user |

### Products *(Bearer token required)*

| Method | Path | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `GET` | `/products` | List products |
| `GET` | `/products/<id>` | Get a product by id |
| `POST` | `/products` | Create a product |

### System

| Method | Path | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `GET` | `/health` | Health check — returns `{"status":"ok"}` |
| `GET` | `/docs` | Swagger UI |
| `GET` | `/redoc` | ReDoc |
| `GET` | `/openapi.json` | OpenAPI 3.0 spec |

## Running Tests

```bash
dart test
dart test --reporter expanded                                # verbose output
dart test test/controllers/auth_controller_test.dart        # single file
```

## Database Migrations

```bash
# Generate a new numbered migration file
dartapi generate migration create_users_table

# Apply all pending migrations
dartapi db migrate

# Preview without applying
dartapi db migrate --dry-run
```
